  "texts": [
    "Previous works have demonstrated its strong performance in knowledge-intensive tasks such as question answering, fact checking, and content recommendation [12,24,32,41].Retrievers interact with external corpus to acquire relevant information.",
    "For open-domain question answering, the Wikipedia corpus [6] is commonly used.",
    "As for retrieval methods, it can broadly be categorized into two types: sparse retrievers and dense retrievers.",
    "Sparse retrievers, such as TF-IDF [37] and BM25 [35], predominantly rely on keyword matching for document retrieval.",
    "These methods determine the relevance between queries and documents by analyzing the occurrence and distribution of keywords within the documents."
  ],
